cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on network monitoring and traffic analysis. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper discusses cyber threats and anomaly detection. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a new approach to simplify and quicken programming and deployment of online traffic analysis functions. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) could be relevant as the paper discusses scalability and efficient implementation of traffic analysis functions. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also possible as the paper proposes a high-level language for writing online traffic analysis tasks.
